# Supabase & RLS

- Assume Row Level Security (RLS) must protect all user data.
- If adding a new table, policy, or query, verify the corresponding RLS policy exists or note that it must be created.
- Never bypass RLS with service-role usage in normal app flows.
- Use the service-role key only in trusted server-only admin code and never in user-request paths unless explicitly required.
- Prefer querying through the authenticated user context for app features.
- When writing queries, select only needed columns.
- Avoid `select('*')` unless the table is very small and the use is justified.
- For joins and nested selects, keep payloads narrow.
- If a query depends on `auth.uid()`, state that clearly in comments or surrounding logic when useful.

## Schema Changes

When suggesting schema changes, include:
- Migration SQL
- RLS policies
- Indexes for expected filters
- Rollback awareness
